{"title": "Two Ages", "description": "LibriVox volunteers bring you 10 recordings of The Two Ages by Ella Wheeler Wilcox.<br>\r\nThis was the Fortnightly Poetry project for January 25, 2026.    <br> ------<br>\r\nAround the age of 8, Wilcox turned to writing poetry as an outlet. When she was 13 years old, her first poem was published. After losing her subscription to The New York Mercury, and being unable to afford to resubscribe, Wilcox thought that if she could get a piece of literature published, she would at least receive a copy of the paper wherein her piece was printed. - Summary by Wikipedia", "duration": 1782, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "340", "name": "Ella Wheeler Wilcox"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/twoages_2602.poem_librivox/twoages_2602.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Multi-version (Weekly and Fortnightly poetry)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "David Lawrence"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "David Lawrence"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "David Lawrence"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Two Ages - read by BK", "readers": [8786], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/twoages_2602.poem_librivox/twoages_wilcox_bk_64kb.mp3", "duration": 196}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Two Ages - read by BWC", "readers": [17576], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/twoages_2602.poem_librivox/twoages_wilcox_bwc_64kb.mp3", "duration": 166}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Two Ages - read by DC", "readers": [16764], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/twoages_2602.poem_librivox/twoages_wilcox_dc_64kb.mp3", "duration": 155}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Two Ages - read by DL", "readers": [2911], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/twoages_2602.poem_librivox/twoages_wilcox_dl_64kb.mp3", "duration": 182}, {"section": 5, "title": "The Two Ages - read by DLS", "readers": [15365], "path": "https://www.archive.org/downloa